class Solution {
    public int removeElement(int[] nums, int val) {
            int index = 0;
            for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
                if(nums[i]!=val){
                    nums[index]=nums[i];
                    index++;
                }
            }
            return index;
    }
}

the code efficiently removes all occurrences of the specified element from the input array and returns the length of the modified array. This is achieved by using a two-pointer approach where one pointer (index) keeps track of the position for non-matching elements.




